title: MIxS Checklist
description: A class with slots assigned for the required, recommended, and optional metadata fields for a specific type sequence, such as genomes, metagenomes, or marker genes. The migs class, which models genomic sequences, is subdivided into checklists for specific taxa: eukaryotes, bacteria, viruses, and plants.

title: Environmental Package
description: A supplement to MIxS Checklists, in the sense of  providing additional terms to describe the specific environement from which a sample was collected.
